choices.text:
riding a moto. On these little motorbikes, Jessie, Jamila and a Tanzanian Poly-technique student (I think he came to teach math and other sciences) are going on an adventure. They are going to view a movie all in frankophonie about an island in africa. So they determine that renting a moto is the best way to get there since we will save money on taxis.

We go to the local gas station to pick up a moto and guess who’s there…….my French friend from Burkina! We met before the airport on the way to Essaouira. Small world. They rent him a motorbike and we venture off.

We are cable of getting the address of the shop through my fractured French. We get to the place at 10:30am expecting the movie to be at 11am and there seem to be nothing to be opened. I call my French friend on the phone only to have him tell me it is an african cultural center…..it is a place where the work of people in the living is shown. The only thing that is there are changing exhibition. The movies are not going on till 4pm. Sigh.
